  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study hypotheasis is that curcumin, a natural compound with a potent antiproliferative
      effect, can improve the efficacy of the standard chemotherapy gemcitabine in patients with
      advanced pancreatic cancer. That is why the patients are given a daily oral dose of 8 gr of
      curcumin along the chemotherapeutic protocol of weekly gemcitabine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
